{"key":"processedPost-26129208","value":{"id":26129208,"first":26128841,"last":26149995,"when":1565413011,"utime":"08/10/19 07:56 AM","content":"It's probably not suitable, at least not without some modifications.&nbsp; Medical autoclaves are intended for tools and towels, etc., not hydrated substrates.&nbsp; Most have a solenoid which opens to suddenly dump pressure at the end of the cycle.&nbsp; That's fine for a scalpel, but if you dump pressure with a jar of grains inside, it's probably going to break the jar, or at the very least dry out the grains.<br />RR","title":"Re: Medical Autoclave advice"}}